author: Pti
title: Air India flight with 122 on board hit by bird - Khaleej Times
text:
Air India flight with 122 on board hit by bird PTI /New Delhi Filed on February 6, 2017 Share 
(Reuters) The aircraft has been grounded and Air India is assessing the damage to the plane A Delhi-bound Air India flight from Bhopal, carrying 122 passengers and crew on board, was diverted to Jaipur on Monday after the aircraft suffered a bird hit. Dubai-Melbourne Qantas flight diverted to Singapore All the passengers deplaned safely after the aircraft landed at Jaipur, an Air India spokesperson said. The aircraft suffered the bird hit during the take off from Bhopal airport this morning, the spokesperson said. The aircraft has been grounded and Air India is assessing the damage to the plane.
